article.story: NEW YORK -- — Joshua Rivera scored 13 points as Fordham beat Fairleigh Dickinson 80-52 on Thursday night. Rivera also had seven rebounds for the Rams (4-3). Will Richardson scored 10 points while shooting 2 for 7 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 5 of 7 from the free throw line. Abdou Tsimbila shot 3 of 4 from the field and 4 for 4 from the line to finish with 10 points. Sean Moore led the way for the Knights (4-5) with 12 points and eight rebounds. Fairleigh Dickinson also got 10 points from Heru Bligen. Joe Munden Jr. also had nine points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
